						               													<description>Front of Box:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;The Exciting new game invented especially for bubblegum card collectors.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Experience the fun of card collecting and trading, card auctions, flipping contests, attic finds and much, much more.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A game the whole family can enjoy.  May be played by 2 to 6 players.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Back of Box:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Now you can have the fun of putting together your own collection of Tobacco Cards, Goudeys, Bowmans, Rookie Cards of your favorite super stars and other rare cards.  Build your collection through trading, card auctions and flipping contests.  Each card is worth points.  You win the game by collecting cards totaling 1,500 points.  you get a starter collection of star cards, common cards and collector's money but then it's up to you.  However, beware of drawing those special cards.  They're full of surprises!  Just when you are about to win you may have to give up your best star card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;An easy-to-play game for baseball card collectors of all ages.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;A great family game that can be played by from 2 to 6 collectors.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;An exciting and fast moving game of skill, luck and fun for beginning and advanced collectors.  New collectors will pick up hobby terminology and learn to recognize names of rare cards.  Seasoned collectors will find that the game recreates real life card collecting experiences.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Here is what players have to say: 'Scott's Baseball Card Game is different every time it is played'...'If you like baseball card collecting, you'll love this game'...'There has never been a game like it.'&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Address on back of box is Scott's Baseball Cards, P.O. Box 12424, Salem, OR 97309&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
